{{CoordDec|51.759710|-1.258102}}[[File:DDeRPortrait.jpg|thumb|upright|The former Director of the OeRC, Prof. [[David De Roure]].<ref name="wst14" />]]
The '''Oxford e-Research Centre''' ('''OeRC''') is part of the [[Department of Engineering Science, University of Oxford|Department of Engineering Science]] within the [[University of Oxford]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ox.ac.uk/about/departments-a_z |title=Departments A-Z &#124; University of Oxford |publisher=Ox.ac.uk |date= |accessdate=2015-10-05}}</ref> in [[England]] and specialises in [[e-Research]] – the use of [[information technology]] to support existing and new forms of research across a wide range of disciplines.
The Centre was founded in 2006<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oerc.ox.ac.uk/about-us |title=About Us &#124; Oxford e-Research Centre |publisher=Oerc.ox.ac.uk |date= |accessdate=2015-10-05}}</ref> and focuses on [[multidisciplinary]] projects, bringing together researchers from across Oxford University and beyond. OeRC has received [[EPSRC]] UK government funding.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://gow.epsrc.ac.uk/NGBOViewGrant.aspx?GrantRef=EP/D055156/1 | title=Oxford Interdisciplinary e-Research Centre – building on e-Science | publisher=[[EPSRC]] | location=UK | accessdate=10 May 2016 }}</ref> The Centre participated in ''SOCIAM: The Theory and Practice of Social Machines'', led in Prof. Sir [[Nigel Shadbolt]] with Prof. [[David De Roure]], Director OeRC, as co-investigator.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://sociam.org/content/university-oxford-department-computer-science-and-oxford-e-research-centre | title=University of Oxford (Department of Computer Science and Oxford e-Research Centre) | website=SOCIAM.org | accessdate=10 May 2016 }}</ref> OeRC is home to over 50 researchers. Disciplines the Centre is involved in are as diverse as [[musicology]] and [[astronomy]], including international collaborations such as the [[Square Kilometre Array]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jb.man.ac.uk/news/2013/SKAwork/ |title=Work starts on world's largest telescope &#124; Jodrell Bank Centre for Astrophysics |publisher=Jb.man.ac.uk |date=2013-11-04 |accessdate=2015-10-05}}</ref>
The Centre was headed by its Director, Prof. [[David De Roure]].<ref name="wst14">{{cite web| url=http://www.webscience.org/category/oerc/ | publisher=[[Web Science Trust]] | work=Archives: Oxford e-Research Centre | title=Oxford e-Research Centre, WSTNET Video: Webinar 2014 – Prof Dave De Roure | date=16 March 2014 | accessdate=10 May 2016 }}</ref> Prof. [[Ron Perrott]], a visiting professor at the OeRC, was awarded an [[Association for Computing Machinery|ACM]] Distinguished Service Award in 2016.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.hpcwire.com/2016/05/04/acm-honors-ron-perrott-2016-distinguished-service-award/ | date=4 May 2016A | title=CM Honors Ron Perrott with Distinguished Service Award | website=HPCwire.com | first=John | last=Russell | accessdate=10 May 2016 }}</ref> In August 2017 the Centre integrated with the Department of Engineering Science, with Dr Wes Amour serving as the new head.<ref name="merge">{{cite web |url=http://www.oerc.ox.ac.uk/news/centre-joins-engineering-science |title=Centre embraces exciting future as it joins the Department of Engineering Science |publisher=OeRC |date=2017-08-01 |accessdate=2017-08-11 }}</ref>
The collaborative Oxford CLARIN Centre is based in the Oxford e-Research Centre.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.clarin.ac.uk/oxford-e-research-centre | title=Oxford e-Research Centre | website=CLARIN.ac.uk | location=UK | accessdate=10 May 2016 }}</ref>
